Title: Conformality, Particle Phenomenology and the Cosmological Constant
Author: Paul H. Frampton
Comments: 11 pages LaTeX. Talk at ORBIS-99, Fort Lauderdale. December 1999
Report-no: IFP-783-UNC
\\
  Conformality is the idea that at TeV scales enrichment of the standard model
particle spectrum leads to conformal invariance at a fixed point of the
renormalization group. Some aspects of conformality in particle phenomenology
and cosmology are discussed.
